# ðŸŽ CeylonStay â€” Host Listing Creation UI (Apple-Style Spec)

## Core UX Strategy (Very Important)

**Mental model:**

> â€œCreate a listing in small, confident steps â€” never overwhelm.â€

Instead of **one long form**, we use a **step-based flow**.

âœ… Apple prefers **guided, linear flows** for complex input.

---

## Overall Structure

### Navigation Pattern

* **Modal flow**
* **Push-based steps**
* **Progress indicator**
* **Cancel at any time**

```
Profile â†’ My Listings â†’ Create New Listing
```

---

## Step Overview

| Step | Purpose                |
| ---- | ---------------------- |
| 1    | Basic Info             |
| 2    | Location               |
| 3    | Details                |
| 4    | Amenities              |
| 5    | Photos                 |
| 6    | Pricing & Availability |
| 7    | Review & Publish       |

---

## Global UI Elements (All Steps)

### Navigation Bar

* Left: `Cancel`
* Title: Step title
* Right: `Next` (disabled until valid)

### Progress Indicator

* Thin progress bar under nav bar
* Height: 3
* Color: Primary Green

---

# STEP 1 â€” Basic Info

### Goal

â€œWhat is this place?â€

---

### Fields (List Style Form)

**1. Listing Title**

* Placeholder:
  `e.g. Cozy Villa in Ella`
* Max: 50 chars
* Font: Body

**2. Property Type**

* Picker (Action Sheet)
* Options:

  * Entire place
  * Private room
  * Shared room

**3. Description**

* Multiline
* Placeholder:
  `Tell guests what makes your place special`
* Max: 500 chars

---

### Layout

* Grouped list
* Section headers

---

# STEP 2 â€” Location

### Goal

â€œWhere is it?â€

---

### Components

**1. Address Search**

* SearchField
* Placeholder:
  `Search for town or area`

**2. Map Preview**

* Height: 220
* Pin placed automatically
* Draggable pin (optional)

**Helper text**

> Guests will see the approximate location after booking.

---

# STEP 3 â€” Property Details

### Goal

â€œWhat does the place offer?â€

---

### Controls (Stepper Style)

| Field     | Min | Max |
| --------- | --- | --- |
| Beds      | 1   | 10  |
| Bathrooms | 1   | 10  |
| Guests    | 1   | 20  |

Apple rule:

> Use steppers for small numeric ranges.

---

# STEP 4 â€” Amenities

### Goal

â€œQuickly select whatâ€™s availableâ€

---

### Layout

* Grid (2 columns)
* Toggle buttons

### Common Amenities

* Wi-Fi
* Air Conditioning
* Parking
* Kitchen
* TV
* Washing Machine

### Toggle Style

* Rounded pill
* Selected: Primary Green
* Unselected: Secondary Background

---

# STEP 5 â€” Photos

### Goal

â€œShow, donâ€™t tellâ€

---

### Photo Picker

* Use system photo picker
* Allow multiple selection
* Max: 10 images

### Photo Grid

* 3 columns
* Drag to reorder
* First photo = cover

**Helper text**

> Your first photo will be the cover image.

---

# STEP 6 â€” Pricing & Availability

### Pricing

**Price per Night**

* Numeric input
* Prefix: `LKR`
* Placeholder:
  `e.g. 8500`

---

### Availability Calendar

* Host can:

  * Mark unavailable dates
  * Block specific days

**Visual Rules**

* Available: White
* Blocked: Gray
* Selected range: Primary Green

---

# STEP 7 â€” Review & Publish

### Goal

â€œConfidence before publishingâ€

---

### Preview Card

* Cover image
* Title
* Location
* Price

---

### Editable Sections

